race.comment: UNTAPPED (6) should run a bold race at the early each-way odds. The first up run over this route was good when in the market, boxing on gamely for third. If anything, this looks slightly easier and he should get every chance from the gate. ZORRO'S FLIGHT (9) resumes. 1200m is short of his best having gotten out to 1700m last time in, but he was racing in some good 3yo races. His recent trial was quite sharp and he'll be strong late. GRINZINGER POD (12) resumes. Her form was mixed last time in but her best runs read well, including running a good sixth in a G3 race in Adelaide. Drawn to get back but Williams being booked is a good lead. DOLLAR CHASER (5) was just fair here last time but had been solid prior at Sale and can figure at big odds. HUSTLE IN HEELS (11) is lightly raced and should be ready for 1200m now.
